<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 08 at 10:09PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southern Donley
County through 1045 PM CDT...
At 1009 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles southwest of Clarendon, moving east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Clarendon, Hedley and Lelia Lake.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
